The Special Adviser to Rivers State Governor on Lands and Survey, Dr Anugbom Anuogha, who was abducted by unknown gunmen in Ada George axis of Port Harcourt, has regained his freedom. Dr Anuoha, who was held captive for 14 days, regained freedom in the early hours of yesterday. The Rivers State Police Public Relations Officer, Nnamdi Omoni, said the pressure mounted by the police and other security agencies in the state on the abductors made them to free the victim. He said that the police are on trail of the kidnappers, to arrest them. Abducted Vanguard columnist freed in Rivers Matron regains freedom, 4 suspected abductors arrested Abducted mother of ex-chairman  regains freedom